SIMPLE: tingle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tingle
<hw>Tin"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Tingled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Tingling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Freq. of
<ets>ting</ets>. Cf. <er>Tinkle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To feel a
kind of thrilling sensation, as in hearing a shrill sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At which both the ears of every one that heareth it shall
tingle.</q> <rj><qau>1 Sam. iii. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To feel a sharp, thrilling pain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pale boy senator yet <qex>tingling</qex> stands.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To have, or to cause, a sharp, thrilling sensation,
or a slight pricking sensation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They suck pollution through their <qex>tingling</qex> vein.</q>
<rj><qau>Tickell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tink</ent>⟦br⟧
